tes","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/32.html",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.htm",{"_":34,"ana":35,"ref":36},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":38},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":40},{"p":41,"rs":42,"damage":46},"Line 1 is inscribed across the upper moulding (which is heavily damaged); the remainder of the text is engraved on the recessed front face, in two columns. The spacing between the columns after the first line is very irregular; column 2 has a half-line gap after line 2, meaning that the lines in the two columns are vertically out of synch after this point.",{"_":43,"ana":44,"ref":45},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":47},"#text_condition.partly_illegible",{"lettering":49,"dimensions":50},"Neatly carved and regular letters, mostly without serifs, but some terminal wedges. Alpha with straight bar; epsilon on occasion has a slightly shorter mid-bar; zeta in form of I with wide horizontals; theta has short detached cross-bar; kappa has full-length arms; mu has vertical first and last, full length mid-strokes; xsi has three equal horiztonal bars; omicron is only slightly smaller than the other letters; pi has extended horizontal; rho has small rounded closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom, with slihgtly variable mid-strokes; phi has small oval eye, with vertical often extended; omega is notably variable, always closed, but ranging from tear-drop to full circle on or even above and detached from the base line.",[51,57,64],{"type":52,"l":53,"from":54,"to":54,"h":55,"unit":56,"atLeast":55,"atMost":55},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","18","mm",{"type":52,"l":58,"from":59,"to":60,"h":61,"unit":56,"atLeast":62,"atMost":63},"Line 2-23","line2","line23","11-15 (with omicron down to 9 and phi up to 20)","11","15",{"type":65,"l":66,"from":67,"to":59,"unit":56},"int